President Donald Trump awarded the Presidential Medal of Freedom to economist Dr. Arthur Laffer, known as the father of supply-side economics. Laffer's theory, famously depicted by the Laffer Curve, argued that lower tax rates incentivize economic growth and increase government revenue. Laffer's economic policies have been influential in shaping the economic reforms of the Reagan administration and the recent tax cuts implemented under President Trump. The article highlights Laffer's achievements and his impact on economic policy.